pr_review_body:
> golangci-lint-action does not support multiple modules in one call,
so we have to run the action separately for each submodule.

@abhinav Are you sure it doesn't support multiple modules in one call? [This issue indicates that you can](https://github.com/golangci/golangci-lint-action/issues/271#issuecomment-1340937024). I would expect the `args` field to accept the module names, just like [here](https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/pull/12023/files#diff-76ed074a9305c04054cdebb9e9aad2d818052b07091de1f20cad0bbac34ffb52R107).

Hi @maxhgerlach, excellent work (and thanks for handling the shutdown race condition I brought up on Slack). 

I left a minor comment about error messages. Since process set IDs aren't supposed to be a public detail, might be nice to change the wording, but not a big deal. Otherwise, I think we are good to land this one!

@tgaddair Before merging, you might to have someone look over any gloo changes, since I am less familiar with that part of the code.

@alirezazolanvari Wow, such a huge PR 💯 

1. I think we need a template for docstring in `CONTRIBUTING.md`
2. Please update `CHANGELOG.md`

you [should](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cat_(Unix)#Useless_use_of_cat) replace `cat ChangeLog | grep -oPz '(?s)(?<=version ${{ steps.bump_version.outputs.ytdl_version }}
{2}).+?(?=
{2,3}version)')` with `grep -oPz '(?s)(?<=version ${{ steps.bump_version.outputs.ytdl_version }}
{2}).+?(?=
{2,3}version)') ChangeLog`

